1
00:00:02,780 --> 00:00:06,200
Repeating seasons...

2
00:00:07,390 --> 00:00:11,500
...and accumulating memories.

3
00:00:12,820 --> 00:00:16,350
Like in childhood...

4
00:00:16,980 --> 00:00:21,700
...I want to believe that I can freely fly in the sky.

5
00:00:22,980 --> 00:00:28,930
When I stumble and look downward...

6
00:00:29,230 --> 00:00:32,550
Tears flow and shine, but...

7
00:00:32,750 --> 00:00:34,900
Back to the ground

8
00:00:34,700 --> 00:00:42,700
A smile heals wounded wings.

9
00:00:42,670 --> 00:00:44,730
Back to the ground

10
00:00:44,780 --> 00:00:52,280
The wind and the earth embrace me.

11
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:59,150
I don't care what anyone says...

12
00:00:59,480 --> 00:01:02,850
...because I believe in myself.

13
00:01:02,900 --> 00:01:09,400
Someday, I will come close...

14
00:01:09,630 --> 00:01:15,100
...to this big, endless dream.

15
00:01:15,100 --> 00:01:21,800
Presented by Central Anime

16
00:01:37,100 --> 00:01:37,940
Dream.

17
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:43,770
A great aspiration that I began
 to hold sometime in the past.

18
00:01:46,150 --> 00:01:51,660
Whether we stumble or fall,
 we never cease to chase after it.

19
00:01:53,720 --> 00:01:54,300
Because...

20
00:01:56,150 --> 00:01:57,070
Because...

21
00:01:57,450 --> 00:02:00,800
Congratulations
on your
Invitational
 Appearance, 
Meiwa Daiichi 
High School

22
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:11,250
The First Date  !

23
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:11,250
 Episode 41(Final)

24
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:11,250
The Pledge For Summer Starts Here !

25
00:02:04,540 --> 00:02:10,780


26
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:16,750
Tachibana, whom would you like to 
tell first how happy you are right now ?

27
00:02:16,750 --> 00:02:17,770
This way, please !

28
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:19,620
This way, also !

29
00:02:21,660 --> 00:02:24,860
Let's see. 
It's probably my parents.

30
00:02:25,460 --> 00:02:27,520
Man, what a liar.

31
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:30,550
Couldn't you have
 said something better ?

32
00:02:31,640 --> 00:02:33,330
It was a national broadcast, after all.

33
00:02:33,330 --> 00:02:37,510
Hey, you guys should come and cheer for me at the Koushien with Hikari.

34
00:02:38,780 --> 00:02:42,450
Moron ! When we go there, we'll be on the field !

35
00:02:42,450 --> 00:02:44,980
We have no business
 in the bleachers !

36
00:02:44,980 --> 00:02:45,810
Right ?

37
00:02:45,810 --> 00:02:46,580
Right !

38
00:02:48,190 --> 00:02:48,900
I guess.

39
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,970
Manager for the baseball club ?

40
00:02:52,970 --> 00:02:56,050
Yeah. If I ask, 
I'm sure they'll let you.

41
00:02:56,050 --> 00:02:57,200
You can count on me.

42
00:02:57,960 --> 00:03:01,810
Wait. I'm a member
 of the archery club.

43
00:03:01,810 --> 00:03:05,340
What ? You aren't going to come and cheer for me ?

44
00:03:05,340 --> 00:03:09,250
Of course I will.
I plan to go to the Koushien, too.

45
00:03:09,250 --> 00:03:11,360
It's no fun just going there, is it ?

46
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:15,180
You'll get to stay at the same inn, from marching into Koushien Stadium to game day.

47
00:03:15,180 --> 00:03:15,970
Right ?

48
00:03:15,970 --> 00:03:19,350
But there are other managers.

49
00:03:19,350 --> 00:03:22,000
Yeah, and there are many
 more who want to do it.

50
00:03:23,190 --> 00:03:24,990
Then that's all the more reason.

51
00:03:26,060 --> 00:03:27,080
What about it ?

52
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:28,680
It feels too presumptuous.

53
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:29,500
I am ?

54
00:03:30,830 --> 00:03:34,110
For me to be a manager.

55
00:03:34,110 --> 00:03:35,580
Do you think so ?

56
00:03:35,580 --> 00:03:39,800
Besides, the manager job isn't something
you can do just because someone asks you.

57
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:46,400
Are you mad ?

58
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:48,080
No, not at all.

59
00:03:49,170 --> 00:03:50,000
Really ?

60
00:03:50,660 --> 00:03:51,870
Really.

61
00:03:55,370 --> 00:03:56,400
Hide-chan.

62
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:57,030
Hm ?

63
00:04:05,040 --> 00:04:06,210
Congratulations.

64
00:04:06,210 --> 00:04:06,850
Yeah.

65
00:04:06,850 --> 00:04:08,400
And thanks.

66
00:04:10,590 --> 00:04:13,710
I'll cheer as hard as
 I can at the Koushien.

67
00:04:14,310 --> 00:04:15,670
Yeah.

68
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:41,590
When I look at your practice swing, it just doesn't seem like you're any good as a hitter.

69
00:04:41,590 --> 00:04:42,760
Shut up.

70
00:04:44,340 --> 00:04:45,200
Hey.

71
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:48,690
So are you mad at her ?

72
00:04:48,690 --> 00:04:53,910
No. It's just that I didn't expect her to turn it down, so I was surprised.

73
00:04:53,910 --> 00:04:56,060
What's so surprising about it ?

74
00:04:56,060 --> 00:04:57,780
I mean, don't you think so ?

75
00:04:57,780 --> 00:04:59,100
In junior high...

76
00:04:59,100 --> 00:05:02,800
...she did pretty well as a long-distance runner for the track and field team...

77
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:06,150
...but she joined the archery club for trivial reasons like how good the "hakama" looks...

78
00:05:06,150 --> 00:05:12,190
...or how great it probably feels when the arrow hits the target, and stuff.

79
00:05:12,190 --> 00:05:14,700
You wouldn't expect her
 to be that committed to it.

80
00:05:15,550 --> 00:05:19,350
I thought she had 
the same dream as me.

81
00:05:19,350 --> 00:05:21,850
I wonder if she actually loves me.

82
00:05:25,310 --> 00:05:26,700
Hold the bat tight, okay ?

83
00:05:27,710 --> 00:05:28,710
Hey.

84
00:05:28,710 --> 00:05:29,200
Hm ?

85
00:05:31,300 --> 00:05:37,200
If you were a pathetic guy who couldn't show even half of his potential without Hikari...

86
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:39,790
...she'd come flying to help you, even if you didn't ask.

87
00:05:39,790 --> 00:05:41,200
Really ?

88
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:44,700
It's because she trusts you that she feels safe to leave you be.





89
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:48,120
So I should be a pathetic guy ?

90
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:50,760
What kind of a guy is pathetic ?

91
00:05:52,020 --> 00:05:53,370
Um...

92
00:05:53,650 --> 00:05:55,440
What are you doing, Hiro ?

93
00:05:55,440 --> 00:05:59,000
You should blow your nose. You need to button up, too !

94
00:06:00,310 --> 00:06:04,000
I told you to do your
homework when you got home.

95
00:06:05,790 --> 00:06:09,700
It's fine, Mrs. Kunimi. I'll be 
sure to keep an eye on Hiro.

96
00:06:10,420 --> 00:06:11,240
I'll keep an eye on him.

97
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:12,300
I'll keep an eye on him.

98
00:06:12,830 --> 00:06:13,900
I'll keep an eye on him. 

99
00:06:14,850 --> 00:06:16,510
It's so pathetic.

100
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:20,560
So what kind of a
 guy is pathetic, really ?

101
00:06:22,370 --> 00:06:26,970
Well, I don't know if Hikari would fall for that kind of a guy, though.

102
00:06:28,210 --> 00:06:30,530
She's a level-headed girl.

103
00:06:30,530 --> 00:06:36,350
She joined the archery club 
because she had her own ideas.

104
00:06:36,350 --> 00:06:37,250
I'm sure of it.

105
00:06:41,460 --> 00:06:45,200
She just chose something
 that would allow her to grow.

106
00:06:46,270 --> 00:06:48,510
She's always been 
firm since she was little.

107
00:06:48,510 --> 00:06:49,880
Since she was little ?

108
00:06:49,880 --> 00:06:51,000
Yeah.

109
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,300
Ever since she was
 in elementary school...

110
00:06:52,300 --> 00:06:55,070
...she's wanted to be a sports journalist and she wrote about it in her essay.

111
00:06:56,950 --> 00:06:59,250
You don't seem to take
 her seriously, though.

112
00:06:59,250 --> 00:07:00,000
Hmm...

113
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:04,580
You guys are alike in that you're both firm and level-headed.

114
00:07:04,580 --> 00:07:06,200
That's why Hikari feels safe with you.

115
00:07:07,270 --> 00:07:11,900
I see. She feels safe 
and leaves me be.

116
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:20,850
I guess it's better to have her feel safe than think of me as a pathetic guy.

117
00:07:23,650 --> 00:07:24,430
Probably.

118
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:26,020
Hmm...

119
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:29,290
Okay, I got it !

120
00:07:30,290 --> 00:07:31,120
Huh ?

121
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:35,150
I see. She feels safe and 
that's why she leaves me alone.

122
00:07:35,150 --> 00:07:37,090
Now I get it.

123
00:07:48,470 --> 00:07:51,420
When we were teammates, 
I used to love that sound.

124
00:07:51,420 --> 00:07:53,300
But now it's a really
 unpleasant sound.

125
00:07:54,220 --> 00:07:57,650
I feel the same way about the sound Noda's mitt makes when he catches your pitches.

126
00:07:57,650 --> 00:07:58,400
Thanks.

127
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:05,300
Hiro, I'm going to be
 the best hitter in Japan.

128
00:08:07,450 --> 00:08:10,000
You should become 
the best pitcher in Japan.

129
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:14,940
And let's meet at the
 Koushien this summer.

130
00:08:19,540 --> 00:08:21,100
Yeah.

131
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:24,200
I can share that dream with you.

132
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:02,550
I'm here.

133
00:09:33,130 --> 00:09:35,650
I'm here at the Koushien.

134
00:09:46,920 --> 00:09:49,080
It starts here, Hide-chan.

135
00:09:56,450 --> 00:09:57,750
Yup, it's perfect.

136
00:09:58,710 --> 00:10:00,100
It's flying away !

137
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:01,540
It's gone.

138
00:10:01,540 --> 00:10:03,250
Is it going ?

139
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:04,150
I said it's gone.

140
00:10:04,150 --> 00:10:06,200
And it's gone ! A homerun !

141
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:08,100
One of the noteworthy
 players of this tournament...

142
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:11,670
...Tachibana Hideo from Meiwa Ichi High School, a second-year player hitting fourth.

143
00:10:11,670 --> 00:10:16,250
He makes his Koushien debut with a huge homerun to the middle of the left field stands.

144
00:10:12,550 --> 00:10:15,650
Well, life is pain.

145
00:10:15,650 --> 00:10:21,000
Don't be blinded by the temporary spotlight
and lose sight of yourself, okay, Hide-chan ?

146
00:10:16,250 --> 00:10:23,080
He hit it really well. He's going to be a tremendous force...

147
00:10:29,270 --> 00:10:30,750
Ah, how frustrating.

148
00:10:36,370 --> 00:10:37,730
Hey...

149
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:40,950
If you get ahead of yourself now, you won't last till summer.

150
00:10:42,950 --> 00:10:46,530
Hideo is getting ahead, 
hitting a big one at the Koushien.

151
00:10:47,450 --> 00:10:48,530
Kunimi !

152
00:10:50,700 --> 00:10:53,170
Newspaper people
 want to interview you !

153
00:10:56,590 --> 00:11:02,320
So can we have a comment from you as a representative of Tachibana Hideo's friends ?

154
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:03,490
What ?!

155
00:11:03,700 --> 00:11:05,190
Tachibana ?!

156
00:11:05,860 --> 00:11:07,150
Hold it right there !

157
00:11:07,150 --> 00:11:09,550
Let me speak about Tachibana !

158
00:11:09,900 --> 00:11:11,550
When we were in
 elementary school...

159
00:11:11,550 --> 00:11:14,950
...he and I competed for the cleanup hitter spot on the Hakusan Angels !

160
00:11:14,950 --> 00:11:18,200
Without my genius, Tachibana would not have become who he is now !

161
00:11:19,230 --> 00:11:21,630
Did Tachibana say something
 before he went to the Koushien ?

162
00:11:21,630 --> 00:11:24,630
Hey ! You ! Listen to me !

163
00:11:35,330 --> 00:11:36,130
Shimada.

164
00:11:36,130 --> 00:11:36,940
Yes ?

165
00:11:36,940 --> 00:11:39,980
Could you take
 a few photos of him ?

166
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:44,610
Oh, but all we needed was his comment.
They said we didn't need any photos.

167
00:11:44,610 --> 00:11:45,270
The editors said there was no need for a photo.

168
00:11:44,610 --> 00:11:46,730
Doesn't matter. 
Please do it anyway.

169
00:11:46,730 --> 00:11:49,460
I'm sure we'll need them 
some time down the road.

170
00:11:50,700 --> 00:11:51,810
Okay.

171
00:12:03,560 --> 00:12:06,080


172
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:06,000
Aim for the Koushien

